---Style----------------
Setting the style of an HTML element, can be done with the style attribute.

1.Background Color
example:
  <body style="background-color: aqua;"> 
2.Text Color
   The CSS color property defines the text color for an HTML element:
   Example:
     <h1 style="color: beige;">This is My Practice</h1> 
3.Fonts
   The CSS font-family property defines the font to be used for an HTML element:
   Example
      <h1 style="font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;">My Name is Mukesh Yadav</h1>

4.Text Size
  The CSS font-size property defines the text size for an HTML element:
  example
   <h1 style="font-size: 200%;">My Name is Mukesh Yadav</h1>

5.Text align
  The CSS text-align property defines the horizontal text alignment for an HTML element:
  Example:
 <h1 style="text-align: center;">My Name is Mukesh Yadav</h1>

 ====Summary=====
<!Doctype HTML>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>CSS Practice</title>
  </head>
  <body style="background-color: aqua;">  

  <h1 style="color: beige;">My Name is Mukesh Yadav</h1> 

  <h1 style="font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;">My Name is Mukesh Yadav</h1>

  <h1 style="font-size: 200%;">My Name is Mukesh Yadav</h1>

  <h1 style="text-align: center;">My Name is Mukesh Yadav</h1>

  </body>
</html>

=========================================================================================================================
Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) is used to format the layout of a webpage.

With CSS, you can control the color, font, the size of text, the spacing between elements, 
how elements are positioned and laid out, what background images or background colors are to be used, 
different displays for different devices and screen sizes, and much more!

Using CSS
CSS can be added to HTML documents in 3 ways:

Inline - 
by using the style attribute inside HTML elements
example:
  <h1 style="color:blue;">A Blue Heading</h1>
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Internal - 
by using a <style> element in the <head> section

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
body {background-color: powderblue;}
h1   {color: blue;}
p    {color: red;}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>This is a heading</h1>
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>

</body>
</html>
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
External - 
by using a <link> element to link to an external CSS file

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>

<h1>This is a heading</h1>
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>

</body>
</html>
==============================================================================
Padding:-
The CSS padding property defines a padding (space) between the text and the border.
p {
  border: 2px solid powderblue;
  padding: 30px;
}

Margin:-
The CSS margin property defines a margin (space) outside the border.

 
